text: When Arthur C. Clarke wrote "Childhood's End" in 1953 it was our own selfishness as humans that limited us as a people and the invading extra-terrestrials in the novel had to use force to shepherd us into living unselfishly, ultimately evolving the human race to a higher form. Now in 2018 in this film, which appears to have a similar "space aliens conquer and run the world" plot, it seems to be the force of the all-powerful invaders and those who obey them that ultimately oppress and limit humanity, not humanity itself. A definite reflection of the times we live in. I'm guessing this is a Leftist propaganda film through and through and that Goodman plays some sort of Trumpian figure who uses the invaders as a way to oppress minorities. Just a guess but it looks like that's the way this film is leaning. Still may go see it though.
